#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:1
msgid "Election Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:3
msgid "Explanation of the Main Procedure Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:4
msgid ""
"The election procedure depends on several parameters, of which the "
"following three are the most important:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:5
msgid "Number of constituencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:6
msgid ""
"Constituency representation: **Entire Parliament** or **Government "
"Majority**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:7
msgid "Government majority"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:9
msgid "These three parameters determine the size of the parliament."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:11
msgid ""
"Each constituency should have a representative in parliament. From the "
"perspective of a constituency, it can make a difference whether its "
"representative sits in the government faction or not. One could therefore"
" require that each constituency has a representative in the government "
"faction. However, since we also want to grant all parties the right to "
"bring as many of their own candidates into parliament as the voters have "
"directly elected, this results in large parliaments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:13
msgid ""
"Number of constituencies * 2 = Number of government seats = "
"ceil(Government majority in % / 100 * Number of parliament seats) <br> "
"Parliament seats ≈ int(200 * Number of constituencies / Government "
"majority in %)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:16
msgid ""
"With 299 constituencies and a government majority of 55%, this would "
"result in int(200 ∗ 299 / 55) = 1087 parliament seats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:18
msgid ""
"If the requirement for representation through the government majority is "
"waived, the parliament size is simply determined by 2 * Number of "
"constituencies. With 299 constituencies, this would result in 598 "
"parliament seats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:20
msgid ""
"Even with the old election procedure with overhang and compensatory "
"mandates, not every constituency had a representative in the government "
"faction, and nobody was bothered by it. How much complete representation "
"of all constituencies in the government faction is worth to society is a "
"societal discussion that cannot be anticipated here. In the simulation, "
"constituency representation is therefore configurable so that both cases "
"can be tested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:23
msgid ""
"Parameter name: **ElectionConfig.constituency_representation** <br> "
"Possible values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:25
msgid "**ENTIRE_PARLIAMENT** (Entire Parliament)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:26
msgid "**GOVERNING_MAJORITY** (Government Majority)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:28
#, python-format
msgid ""
"When a yes/no question, such as \"Which of two parties should govern?\" "
"is decided by voters with only small percentage differences, the result "
"is more likely due to chance than voter intent. There are always people "
"who make their decision only in the voting booth, and had the election "
"been just one day later or earlier, they might have decided differently. "
"Brexit with 51.9% for \"Leave\" and 48.1% for \"Remain\" was actually "
"such a decision where both groups were essentially equal in size. They "
"could have just as well drawn lots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:30
msgid ""
"To avoid such stochastic effects, it makes sense to introduce a \"minimum"
" winner margin\" to win a voting round. This margin can be specified in "
"percentage of votes or in mandates, or can also be expressed as a "
"qualified majority. In the simulation, there is the "
"**SuperMajorityMargin** class to express a margin either in seats or in "
"percent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:33
msgid "A winner margin makes sense at two points in the procedure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:34
msgid ""
"As the possibly granted parliament majority. So that the government "
"retains its majority even if someone is sick, it should have, for "
"example, 10 seats more than half of the parliament seats. Or it should "
"have so many more seats that it has around 5% more votes than the rest of"
" parliament. The parameter to set the \"parliament margin\" and thus "
"indirectly the parliament majority is "
"**ElectionConfig.parliament_majority_margin**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:35
msgid ""
"As the winner threshold of a single voting round. To win a round, a "
"contestant must exceed 50% by a small minimum margin. This is "
"configurable via **ElectionConfig.ballot_majority_margin** (default: 2%, "
"i.e. a contestant needs at least 52%)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:37
msgid "Global Configuration in the Simulation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md:38
msgid ""
"In the simulation, the "
"[`ElectionConfig`](../../src/ipres/election_config.py) class holds all "
"parameters that are valid for the entire election. These are in detail:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "Parameter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "Brief Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "constituencies_config"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "Table of constituencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "participating_parties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "Participating parties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "parliament_majority_margin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"\"Parliament margin\" in seats or percent. How many parliament seats or "
"vote percent the government should have more than the opposition. See "
"explanation above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "ballot_majority_margin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Minimum margin above 50% a contestant must reach in a single voting "
"round. Default: 2% (i.e. 52%). See explanation above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "draw_lots_strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Default method for resolving ties. Can be overridden in individual voting"
" rounds. Default value: RANDOM (random)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "seed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Seed value for the random generator. Default: None (seed value is chosen "
"randomly.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "constituency_representation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Constituency representation. Possible values: ENTIRE_PARLIAMENT, "
"GOVERNING_MAJORITY. See explanation in the previous chapter. Default: "
"ENTIRE_PARLIAMENT"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Output language for tables and charts. Possible values: `Language.DE` "
"(German, default), `Language.EN` (English). Affects column headers, "
"captions, chart titles, and number formatting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "seat_distribution_method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Default method for proportional seat distribution used by "
"`SeatDistributor` and `ElectionEvaluator`. Possible values: "
"`SAINTE_LAGUE`, `D_HONDT`, `HARE_NIEMEYER`. Default: `SAINTE_LAGUE`. Can "
"be overridden in the individual evaluator classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "quota_correction_strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Default strategy for quota correction when parties have an odd seat "
"count, used by `ConstituencyCountDeterminer` and `ElectionEvaluator`. "
"Possible values: `FAVOR_LARGE_PARTIES`, `FAVOR_SMALL_PARTIES`, "
"`PROPORTIONAL`, `PROPORTIONAL_REVERSED`, `RANDOM`, `NEGOTIATED`. Default:"
" `FAVOR_LARGE_PARTIES`. Can be overridden in the individual evaluator "
"classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid "constituency_allocation_method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/global_configuration.md
msgid ""
"Default algorithm for constituency assignment used by "
"`ConstituencyAssigner` and `ElectionEvaluator`. Possible values: "
"`OPTIMAL`, `GREEDY`, `STABLE_MATCHING`. Default: `OPTIMAL`. Can be "
"overridden in the individual evaluator classes."
msgstr ""

